The paper presents a new randomized algorithm for solving the all-pairs shortest path problem in dense directed graphs with arbitrary edge weights. The algorithm uses a tool from circuit complexity, namely the Razborov-Smolensky polynomials, to efficiently reduce a matrix product over the $(\min,+)$ algebra to a relatively small number of rectangular matrix products over ${\mathbb F}_2$. This suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of dense graphs, which could lead to a classification under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of randomized and deterministic algorithms also suggests a possible classification under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
